Maybe this can clarify something: usually when people talk about the character <code>&#39;
&#39;</code> (decimal 10 on the <a href="http://www.asciitable.com/" rel="nofollow noreferrer">ascii table</a>, meaning <b>new line</b>), which is one character, rather than the string <code>&quot;
&quot;</code> (ascii 92 110), which are two characters. Note: <code>&#39;</code> vs <code>&quot;</code>. Nobody uses &quot;
&quot; as a record separator btw. If you do perhaps you arrive at @sidgate&#39;s approach, but I guess, you don&#39;t want to get there anyway.
